          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ACE-Step 1.5 Turbo multi-model API enables efficient concurrent inference across diverse AI models, reducing latency and resource overhead for API-driven applications. This guide targets experienced teams seeking to leverage its capabilities in production."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Architecture of ACE-Step 1.5 Turbo Multi-Model API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The API is built on a microservices architecture that supports dynamic model loading and request routing. Key components include a load balancer, model registry, and inference engine. It handles multiple models by isolating them in containers, ensuring fault tolerance and scalability. Teams can configure model priorities and resource limits via API endpoints, allowing fine-grained control over inference pipelines."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integration Steps for ACE-Step 1.5 Turbo"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Begin by installing the client SDK compatible with your stack (e.g., Python, Node.js). Authenticate using API keys, then initialize the client with your endpoint URL. Use the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/v1/models",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint to list available models and the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/v1/infer",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint to submit inference requests. Implement retry logic with exponential backoff for transient errors, and monitor response headers for rate-limiting cues."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance Metrics and Optimization"
          }
        ]
      },
